  "text": "DNA probe assays have also been developed for the rapid detection of Listeria species but are not yet available for the rapid and specific detection of L. monocytogenes from enrichment broth cultures of foods. A commercially available DNA probe assay (Gene-Trak Systems, Framingham, Mass.) uses a fluorescein-labeled DNA probe targeted to a Listeria species-specific rRNA sequence for rapid detection of Listeria species in foods [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
